{"sections":[],"abstract":[{"text":"Manages PID files for tracking running virtual machines.","type":"text"}],"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/spooktacularkit\/pidfile"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"kind":"symbol","hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit"]]},"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"minor":3,"patch":0},"metadata":{"title":"PIDFile","modules":[{"name":"SpooktacularKit"}],"navigatorTitle":[{"text":"PIDFile","kind":"identifier"}],"externalID":"s:15SpooktacularKit7PIDFileO","symbolKind":"enum","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"enum"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"PIDFile"}],"roleHeading":"Enumeration","role":"symbol"},"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/PIDFile","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"topicSections":[{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/PIDFile\/fileName"],"generated":true,"title":"Type Properties","anchor":"Type-Properties"},{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/PIDFile\/isProcessAlive(_:)","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/PIDFile\/isRunning(bundleURL:)","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/PIDFile\/read(from:)","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/PIDFile\/remove(from:)","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/PIDFile\/terminate(bundleURL:gracePeriod:)","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/PIDFile\/write(to:)"],"generated":true,"title":"Type Methods","anchor":"Type-Methods"}],"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"platforms":["macOS"],"languages":["swift"],"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"enum"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"PIDFile"}]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"content":[{"text":"Overview","anchor":"overview","level":2,"type":"heading"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Each running VM writes a PID file at"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"~\/.spooktacular\/vms\/<name>.vm\/pid"},{"type":"text","text":". The file contains the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"process ID of the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"spook start"},{"type":"text","text":" process that owns the VM."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Other commands ("},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"stop"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"list"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"ip"},{"type":"text","text":") read the PID file to"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"determine whether a VM is running and to signal the process."}]},{"text":"PID File Lifecycle","anchor":"PID-File-Lifecycle","level":2,"type":"heading"},{"type":"orderedList","items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"code":"spook start","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" writes the PID file before booting the VM.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"code":"spook stop","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" reads the PID file and sends SIGTERM.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"code":"spook start","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" installs a SIGTERM handler that gracefully","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"stops the VM, removes the PID file, and exits.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"If the process crashes, the PID file becomes stale.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/PIDFile\/isProcessAlive(_:)","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":" detects stale PID files by checking","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"whether the recorded process is still running.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}]},{"text":"Thread Safety","anchor":"Thread-Safety","level":2,"type":"heading"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type"